__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
.env.dev
.pytest_cache/
# .claude/ shared project config is tracked (settings.json + CLAUDE.md);
# only the personal/local overrides file stays ignored.
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/worktrees/
*.bak
# Spec 021 — engine monitor SLOG (ephemeral; durable provenance is the graph)
.agency/monitor.log
.agency/monitor.log.*
# Spec 126 — research-ingest source corpus (subagent-isolated Google Doc
# ingest writes here; durable provenance is the ingested-source Artefact
# in the graph, not the file).
.agency/sources/
# Spec 129 — per-project Dramatica fragment overlay (author-extensible).
.agency/dramatica-fragments-overlay.yaml
# Spec 292 — `.agency/sessions/` is COMMITTED (user directive 2026-06-16): the
# session graph + archived session Documents are durable provenance, like the
# graph DB itself (Spec 020), so a session restores across clones.
# User directive 2026-06-19: `.agency/session.db` is SNAPSHOTTED, not tracked. The
# live binary churns every session + is 96% ephemeral Event noise; the DURABLE graph
# is exported to portable SQL in `.agency/sql/` (`scripts/session-snapshot export`)
# and restored on SessionStart when the db is missing. (PR #194/Jules also untracked
# it — the stop-hook was committing it every turn, a CI-loop.) So the binary is ignored:
.agency/session.db
# Literal '${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}' directory from an unexpanded env var — never real.
${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}
# SQLite databases + their WAL/journal sidecars (local/transient — never commit).
# `*.db` ignores every SQLite binary repo-wide (session.db, toolcalls.db,
# codegraph.db, …); the DURABLE graph travels as portable SQL snapshots
# (`.agency/sql/`), not the churning binary.
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
# CodeGraph: ignore the ENTIRE `.codegraph/` working dir (codegraph's regenerated
# self-un-ignoring `.gitignore`, daemon pid/sockets, WAL/shm). Git does not descend
# into an excluded directory, so none of codegraph's per-sync churn ever shows.
# `.codegraph/codegraph.db` is no longer tracked (untracked 2026-06-20): the ~13MB
# index churns on every reindex and is a local rebuild artefact — `codegraph init`
# regenerates it per machine, so it stays out of version control like the other db
# binaries above.
.codegraph/
# Spec 336 — ephemeral tool-call capture store (local; distilled by the Stop-hook export)
.agency/toolcalls.db
.agency/toolcalls.db-*
